headline: Wells Fargo (WFC): Assessing the Bank’s Valuation After a Year of Strong Shareholder Returns

In that time frame, the stock edged up about 1% while returns remain strong over the past year. See our latest analysis for Wells Fargo. Wells Fargo’s share price has mostly moved sideways in recent weeks, but its steady climb over the past year stands out, with a one-year total shareholder return of 41.7%.
